description:
Training up a child for the Lord is a task not only for parents but also for you and the church. But, how should we train our children in a godly manner? How are we going to bring them to Jesus?

This #short clip from the Global Campmeeting sermon, “Seventh-day Adventist Education: Bringing Children to Jesus  #Campmeeting” https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=iVbSIsA_LDc&list=PL-k2Gb-DBYo9tb9fHW_AxGxJ1R8MpNnpa&index=33 serves as a reminder of our divine commission and duty to lead our children to Christ and teach them the godly ways that God desires every child to know. Training a child entails more than just disciplining them; it also involves modeling the appropriate behavior and attitude they must possess.

“Train up a child in the way he should go, and when he is old he will not depart from it.” — Proverbs 22:6

Watch the video to learn more about how we will train and lead our children to Jesus.
